definition.value: A dTDP-sugar having 4-dehydro-6-deoxy-alpha-D-glucose as the sugar component.  It is an intermediate in dTDP-rhamnose biosynthesis.
A derivative of 17alpha-estradiol having beta-glucosiduronic acid and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl groups attached at the 3- and 17-positions respectively.

A chlorophenylethane that is 1,1,1-trichloro-2,2-diphenylethane substituted by additional chloro substituents at positions 4 of the phenyl substituents. It is a commonly used organochlorine insecticide.
A member of the class of  phenylhydrazines that is phenylhydrazine substituted by a hydroxymethyl group at position 4.
